  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Increasing capacity of the healthcare system to respond to the emergency in Eastern Ukraine (Luhansk oblast NGCA)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The proposal is linked to the HRP 2022 project - HUKR22-HEA-186083-1.

Due to the conflict escalation started on the 24th of February 2022, the situation in Ukraine has changed dramatically. In terms of health the scope of needs has changed completely. Geographically, the conflict line in the Donbas region has moved and unfortunately new conflict areas have appeared these facts have created new areas of intervention. Thematically, massive new health needs have emerged due to the open conflict.  
 
In April 2022 MdM received the renewal of the accreditation for next 6 months in Luhanska oblast NGCA. As the key interventions to respond to the current needs MdM plans to provide emergency life-saving humanitarian assistance to conflict affected people in Luhanska oblast. To address the existing gaps with availability of services and goods in the area MdM plans to deliver medical and non-medical items to health facilities and directly to pregnant women. With consideration of the current situation the life-saving medical equipment, consumables, medications and PPE/IPC items will be prioritized within support delivered to health facilities. To complement this MdM will procure and distribute maternity kits to pregnant women in the area aiming to ensure the availability of the minimum required package with medical and hygiene items for safe delivery and the first months of a newborn child.</narrative>
  </description>
